00:12:09,920 --> 00:12:12,800
 This is the creative process that you see

308
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:15,000
 in Genesis 1 and Genesis 2.

309
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,680
 The Spirit, through the spoken word of God,

310
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:20,680
 takes things that are formless, gives them form,

311
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:22,520
 and then moves them towards their fullness,

312
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:26,120
 a place of shalom that God describes as very good.

313
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:28,400
 And so what we see, the first thing we learn

314
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:31,880
 about the Holy Spirit hovering over a formless,

315
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:34,560
 dark kind of void, and then bringing it

316
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:38,080
 into this beautiful creation, is that the Spirit's intent

317
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:42,740
 always is to take disorder and bring it to order.

318
00:12:42,740 --> 00:12:44,320
 The Spirit is at work in that.

319
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:45,840
 We've been telling you a little bit about that

320
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:46,920
 over the last number of weeks,

321
00:12:46,920 --> 00:12:49,700
 but that's the first movement of the Spirit.

322
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:51,960
 Our introduction to the Spirit is one who takes things

323
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:54,920
 that are disordered and moves it to order.

324
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:57,680
 And then we know what happens next, right?

325
00:12:57,680 --> 00:13:00,480
 In Genesis 3, Adam and Eve decide to sin.

326
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:02,320
 And in their rebellion against what God had called them

327
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:04,720
 to do, a division takes place.

328
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:07,100
 They are actually, as part of that division,

329
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:09,280
 they are thrown out of the garden,

330
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:11,120
 which really was a biblical way of saying

331
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:12,240
 out of God's presence.

332
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:15,320
 So the Spirit was there, hovering over creation,

333
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:17,320
 taking things into its perfect order.

334
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:19,440
 Then sin takes place with humanity,

335
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:21,720
 and suddenly a divide comes between humanity

336
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:25,960
 and the Spirit of God, from humanity and the triune Godhead.

337
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:28,840
 And that division then basically becomes

338
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:30,960
 the movement of the rest of Scripture.

339
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:32,680
 The rest of Scripture is humanity going,

340
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:35,760
 how do we get back to that relationship we had

341
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:38,560
 before sin was a reality?

342
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:42,480
 And this division and the casting out of humanity

343
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:45,160
 from the presence of God becomes humanity's big focus.

344
00:13:45,160 --> 00:13:47,700
 This is why, in Genesis 11, they build a tower

345
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:49,480
 to try to get back up to that presence.

346
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:51,700
 They think if they can just get back up to the heavens

347
00:13:51,700 --> 00:13:54,920
 somewhere, then they can reconcile that Spirit

348
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:57,240
 and that presence, but that's not how God is going to do it.

349
00:13:57,240 --> 00:13:59,880
 In fact, God comes and He breaks down that tower,

350
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:02,640
 and He basically says, we're gonna do this a different way.

351
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:05,600
 The next movement, therefore, of the Spirit that we see

352
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:08,260
 takes place in Exodus chapter three.

353
00:14:08,260 --> 00:14:13,260
 Moses, walking around, suddenly sees a burning bush.

354
00:14:13,260 --> 00:14:16,740
 The Spirit suddenly manifested beautifully

355
00:14:16,740 --> 00:14:19,160
 in this burning bush, and Moses goes over to it,

356
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:20,160
 and we know what happens, right?

357
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:23,000
 As he goes over to the burning bush,

358
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:25,120
 God calls out from the bush and says,

359
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:27,920
 Moses, Moses, don't come any further forward,

360
00:14:27,920 --> 00:14:31,240
 for the ground that you're standing on is what?

361
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:33,880
 Holy ground, holy ground.

362
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:37,000
 Not that Moses was holy, not that the ground

363
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:39,840
 was some special kind of ground that was sacred and holy.

364
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:43,120
 No, it was the presence of God, the Spirit of God

365
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:45,680
 revealed once more towards humanity

366
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:47,880
 that became this holy space.

367
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:49,620
 And when God says, take off your sandals

368
00:14:49,620 --> 00:14:51,240
 and step onto this holy ground,

369
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:54,120
 what He's saying is, I wanna fill the flesh, Moses,

370
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:56,280
 I wanna fill your flesh with my Spirit.

371
00:14:56,280 --> 00:14:58,320
 There's gonna be a communing again

372
00:14:58,320 --> 00:15:01,040
 that was like what it was in the garden before.

373
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:02,640
 We wanna commune now together,

374
00:15:02,640 --> 00:15:05,400
 because God is beginning to change

375
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:08,280
 and draw humanity back to Himself.

376
00:15:08,280 --> 00:15:10,600
 So the starting point is that the Spirit

377
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:11,980
 is disordered, the order.

378
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:14,840
 The next thing is that He is holy.

379
00:15:14,840 --> 00:15:17,200
 And that holiness, the holiness of God,

380
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:18,680
 and the holiness of His Spirit

381
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:20,400
 becomes the way that humanity understands

382
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,460
 its separation from the Spirit.

383
00:15:22,460 --> 00:15:25,680
 The next movement is that God then appears

384
00:15:25,680 --> 00:15:27,480
 by His Spirit on a mountain, Mount Sinai,

385
00:15:27,480 --> 00:15:29,560
 also a part of the Exodus narrative.

386
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:32,800
 And up on the mountain, something very special takes place.

387
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:36,900
 On the mountain, the law is given, the law is poured out.

388
00:15:36,900 --> 00:15:38,040
 That's the Old Testament.

389
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:40,680
 First of all, the 10 laws, the 10 commandments,

390
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:42,520
 then eventually the Levitical law,

391
00:15:42,520 --> 00:15:45,440
 all poured out through the power of the presence

392
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:49,000
 of the Spirit on a mountain, and only one person, Moses,

393
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,520
 is able to go up into that presence

394
00:15:50,520 --> 00:15:52,480
 and see God face to face.

395
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:55,080
 So this one person goes up, sees God face to face,

396
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:56,920
 the law is given, and the law,

397
00:15:56,920 --> 00:15:58,160
 this is the best way to understand it,

398
00:15:58,160 --> 00:16:00,760
 the law is birthed by the Spirit

399
00:16:00,760 --> 00:16:03,800
 to explain to us the character of God.

400
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:05,260
 Often when we think of the 10 commandments,

401
00:16:05,260 --> 00:16:07,040
 we think the 10 commandments are basically

402
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:10,100
 a bunch of rules to make us live a boring life, right?

403
00:16:10,100 --> 00:16:12,680
 Like a bunch of rules that we have to kind of adhere to

404
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:15,360
 or check up on a list just to make ourselves feel better

405
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:17,080
 or to think that we're gonna be

406
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:18,400
 in some better relationship with God,

407
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:20,400
 but actually that's not what the law was about.

408
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:23,720
 See, the law was actually about kind of communicating

409
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:26,560
 to humanity who God is.

410
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:29,280
 So when God says, "You will have no other God before me,"

411
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:33,940
 he's explaining his character of loyalty and steadfastness.

412
00:16:33,940 --> 00:16:35,880
 When he says, "You will not commit murder,"

413
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:39,840
 what he's saying about himself is, "I am a God of life.

414
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:44,520
 "I am a God of giving, not a God of taking."

415
00:16:44,520 --> 00:16:47,260
 So each of the laws represents some character of God

416
00:16:47,260 --> 00:16:49,700
 that God is explaining, and it's the Spirit

417
00:16:49,700 --> 00:16:51,400
 that births the character of God.

418
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:53,280
 Are you with us still so far?

419
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:54,360
 Is this okay?

420
00:16:54,360 --> 00:16:55,680
 Okay, hang with me, hang with me.

421
00:16:55,680 --> 00:16:56,760
 Here's the fourth one.

